ent-CMAnestheticTankFilled-name = anesthetic tank
ent-CMAnestheticTankFilled-desc = A tank with an N2O/O2 gas mix.

ent-RMCGasTankOxygenFilled-name = oxygen tank
ent-RMCGasTankOxygenFilled-desc = A tank containing pressurized oxygen for breathing.

ent-RMCEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-name = emergency oxygen tank
ent-RMCEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-desc = An easily portable tank for emergencies. Contains very little oxygen, rated for survival use only. It can hold 0.66 L of gas.

ent-RMCExtendedEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-name = extended-capacity emergency oxygen tank
ent-RMCExtendedEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-desc = An emergency tank with extended capacity. Technically rated for prolonged use. It can hold 1.5 L of gas.

ent-RMCDoubleEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-name = double emergency oxygen tank
ent-RMCDoubleEmergencyOxygenTankFilled-desc = A high-grade dual-tank emergency life support container. It holds a decent amount of oxygen for its small size. It can hold 2.5 L of gas.

ent-RMCGasTankPhoronFilled-name = phoron tank
ent-RMCGasTankPhoronFilled-desc = A tank of liquid phoron. WARNING: Phumes are extremely dangerous.

